I've issued this call before, but if you're a gym owner get rid of half of the treadmills and stationary bikes no one uses and put an air hockey table or foosball table there instead. For free play of course no need to milk people excessively. 100% better cardio and far more fun.

The only reason no one puts fun games like air hockey in gyms is ideologically people force themselves to pretend it has to be this Spartan self-disciplinary thing instead of sportive amusement. Anyone who has played serious foosball knows you almost drop dead after a few rounds.

It's the type of thing that you have to have personal experience with to understand, but St. Paisios is the type of saint who has a specific talent to answer these theological questions that people worry about for years in a brief throwaway sentence and just wave them off easily.

Like someone will worry about a specific doctrinal issue and be all shaken about it trying not to lose hope and have a crisis of faith and then St. Paisios will just say "oh, you just have to say this prayer and then it's ok, don't get too worried about it" and it's simply solved
